rComments: She (unnecessarily) complicated a general ed course.  She took a topic as broad as the history of life and turned it into detailed lessons on information as minute as the sternum of pterodactyls, for example.  Seriously, pterodactyls weren't that important in the history of life and i cant believe she expected us to waste time memorizing this info

really smart person, knows her material but not the best teacher.  tests are way hard.  loves dinosaurs and rocks and science and expects you to as well if you take her class.  shows funny film clips.

If you are interested in paleontology, this course is a great start. The instructor avoided useless memorization routines and,instead, focused on the function, purpose,and theory behind vertebrate morphology. The only real problem is that she is quite distractingly attractive. Suggestion: tone it down in the looks department a bit will yaâ€¦geeze.
